 {"id":"frankenpandas-rj6u","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: merge/join/concat live oracle parity drifts","description":"Found while building frankenpandas-t7no merge/join/concat conformance matrix.\\n\\n1. dataframe_concat axis=1 outer with left index [\"a\", \"c\"], right index [\"b\", \"c\"], integer columns left_val=[1,3], right_val=[20,30]. Expected live pandas upcasts non-missing values to floats because outer alignment introduces missing values: left_val [1.0, null, 3.0], right_val [null, 20.0, 30.0]. Actual FrankenPandas preserves ints for non-missing values: left_val [1, 3] at aligned positions and right_val [30, 20] non-missing values as ints in drift report.\\n\\n2. series_join outer with left index [\"a\", \"c\"] values [1.0,3.0], right index [\"b\",\"c\"] values [20.0,30.0]. Expected live pandas index [\"a\",\"b\",\"c\"] with missing left at b. Actual FrankenPandas index [\"a\",\"c\",\"b\"] and values aligned to that order.\\n\\nImpact: join/concat index alignment and dtype promotion differ from pandas for outer alignment cases with missing rows.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T06:38:48.200587044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T08:18:30.221642843Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T08:18:30.219823094Z","close_reason":"Resolved outer join ordering and concat axis=1 numeric promotion parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-rm2mv","title":"fd90.102: README claims DataFrameIoExt covers 'all formats' but IPC stream has no trait method (7/8)","description":"fd90.74-101 README audit. Line 150 reads 'All formats accessible through DataFrameIoExt trait methods on DataFrame.' but the trait at crates/fp-io/src/lib.rs has only 11 methods (verified with awk + grep): to_parquet, to_parquet_bytes, to_csv_file, to_json_file, to_excel_file, to_excel_bytes, to_jsonl_file, to_feather_file, to_feather_bytes, to_sql, to_sql_with_options. That covers 7 of the 8 documented IO formats; the Arrow IPC stream format (write_ipc_stream_bytes / read_ipc_stream_bytes) has NO trait method — it is only reachable through the standalone functions. So 'All formats' is wrong. Fix: rewrite the line to specify which formats are reachable through the trait (CSV/JSON/JSONL/Parquet/Excel/Feather/SQL — 7 of 8) and note that Arrow IPC stream uses the standalone read_ipc_stream_bytes / write_ipc_stream_bytes functions. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T10:02:26.056974773Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:03:34.881234430Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:03:34.878531819Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenpandas-rnzg","title":"pandas: DataFrame.pivot_table aggfunc='first' with margins=True parity","description":"py signature:\ndf.pivot_table(values=\"v\", index=\"i\", columns=\"c\", aggfunc=\"first\", margins=True)\n\nCurrent fp-frame base pivot_table supports aggfunc=\"first\", but pivot_table_with_margins and pivot_table_with_margins_name in crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs reject anything outside sum/mean/count/min/max when margins are enabled. Extend margins support to first so the helper matches the single-value pivot path.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T16:56:14.375263709Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T17:16:50.374992244Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T17:16:50.373094351Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
